    "actor_description": "It surges up hot and immediate, and I clamp down so hard it feels like biting metal. My jaw locks; my tongue presses against my teeth; my hands want to do something-hit, throw, shove-and I keep them still by force. I take a measured breath like it's a rule I have to follow, and the anger doesn't go away; it just gets packed tighter, louder, closer to the surface.",
    "description_text": "{actor} holds themself unnaturally steady-jaw set, shoulders tight, movements clipped and over-controlled. Their face stays composed in a way that reads practiced rather than calm, and any words that come out arrive carefully shaped, as if they're managing an explosion one syllable at a time.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear a hard swallow, breath measured through the nose, and the faint grind of teeth-silence with pressure behind it, like a door being held shut.",
        "tactile": "The air feels charged. A body is rigid with restraint-heat, tension, and tiny tremors contained under stillness."
